title: Warren Hills football team beats Somerville on senior night (PHOTOS)
text:
Shane Deemer carried the load for the Warren Hills Regional High School football team on senior night Friday. 
Deemer took 26 carries for 156 yards and a touchdown as the Blue Streaks defeated Somerville 14-7 in a Mid-State 38 Raritan Division game. 
Warren Hills QB Cooper Gabrich connected with Carsen Johnson for a one-handed, 39-yard touchdown pass. 
The Blue Steaks scored all of their points in the second quarter. The entire second half was scoreless. 
Warren Hills also conducted its senior night on Friday, during which the family of Evan Murray was recognized. Murray, a senior, died Sept. 25 after suffering a ruptured spleen during a game against Summit. 
Scroll through the gallery atop this post to see images from Warren Hills' win.
